## M22.1(4/8): `pre` block (multi-line `pre INDENT body OUTDENT`) is reserved in V1.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 39 (M22.1 "fake-surface audit"): the M19-era
## grammar accepted both `pre <expr>` (expression-modifier) and
## `pre INDENT body OUTDENT` (statement block) shapes, but emit
## had no handler for either — they fell through to a default
## arm that produced `@compileError("rig: emitter does not yet
## support pre_block")`. The user got a confusing Zig compile
## error rather than a clean Rig diagnostic.
##
## V1 policy: only `pre_param` (compile-time function parameters
## via `sub f(pre x: Int, y: Int)`) is supported. That form is
## fully wired through sema + emit (lowers to Zig
## `comptime x: i32`) and is used in real examples. The
## expression / block forms remain reserved for a future
## compile-time computation arc; surfacing them as Rig errors
## prevents misuse and preserves the design space.

sub main()
  pre                  # error: `pre` block reserved
    x = 42
    print(x)
